text: Moorang is a locality in the Scenic Rim Region, Queensland, Australia. ==Census Data== Moorang has a population of 43 at the . The locality contains 22 households, which in all contain 23 males and 23 females with a median age of 37, 1 year below the national average. The average weekly household income is $1,343, $95 below the national average. == References == Category:Scenic Rim Region Category:Localities in Queensland
